messages.content: What is the purpose of comfyui-textarea-keybindings?
The purpose of comfyui-textarea-keybindings is to add keybindings to the textarea in ComfyUI.
What are some features of comfyui-textarea-keybindings?
Some features of comfyui-textarea-keybindings include auto closing brackets, quick travel by tab, annotation syntax, and undo history for keybindings.
How does the auto close brackets feature work in comfyui-textarea-keybindings?
In comfyui-textarea-keybindings, when you type an opening bracket, it will automatically insert the corresponding closing bracket based on the selection range.
What happens when you press the Tab key in comfyui-textarea-keybindings?
When you press the Tab key in comfyui-textarea-keybindings, it selects the next word (including blanks after trimming).
How can you toggle annotation in comfyui-textarea-keybindings?
You can toggle annotation in comfyui-textarea-keybindings by pressing Ctrl + /.
Does comfyui-textarea-keybindings have any custom nodes associated with it?
No, comfyui-textarea-keybindings does not have any custom nodes associated with it.
What is the annotation syntax used in comfyui-textarea-keybindings?
The annotation syntax used in comfyui-textarea-keybindings is /* ... */.
